Text.Value: My mum said if you can't play nicely, don't play at all. You've not been very nice.
The Bladder's Mouth?
Whoa, I know you - you're in the gazette today! Saying you're a proper hero-sort!
Calm down. I'm just buying a paper. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
F-fine. Here's your c-copy.
Not right now.
Oh piss... I mean the Baldur's Mouth Gazette, sorry! Please don't tell Mister Ettvard, he'd be ever so cross.
Growl at the weeping child.
Not to worry, there's a new edition every day!
I'll take a copy of the Gazette. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
It's real exciting issue, enjoy!
Nice to see youse again! Today's edition's cheap, if you fancy it. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
No thanks.
N... No. Mister Ettvard said to be m-more assertive. Go away, meanie!
AHH! Okayokayokay, just take one and leave me alone!
Pleasepleaseplease don't hurt me!
Sure, I'll take a copy. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
Good day, guv'nor, I gots a copy of the Bladder's Mouth Gazette fresh off the presses for you - good price, too! ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
If you want to read about it, you'll have to buy a copy. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
No thanks.
Get your Gazette here! Only... Oh. Oh no. You're that nasty person from today's edition -
If you change your mind you know where to find me!
Cor, thanks! Come back tomorrow for the next edition.

Synopsis: Dialog with a paper seller on the edge of the Steeps Strake Market.
